verbose_text: Analysis made on the vitamin composition of the dry leaves of Amaranthus cruentus (known locally as Aleefu) and Solanum macrocarpon (known locally as Gboma) indicates appreciable levels of beta-carotene (63.0 mg/100 g and 64.0 mg/100 g) and ascorbic acid (1.5 mg/100 g and 2.4 mg/100 g), respectively [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
